-- Toyota sees 2008 U.S. sales up 1 percent
-- 
-- Tue Dec 25, 2007 1:08am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/25/us-toyota-sales-idUST17864020071225

 

 NAGOYA, Japan  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T ) expects to sell 2.64 million vehicles in the United States in 2008, up about 1 percent from an estimated 2.62 million this year, a top executive said on Tuesday. 

 In Asia excluding Japan, Toyota expects to raise sales by 20 percent to 1.58 million vehicles, of which about 700,000 will be in China for a rise of 43 percent, Executive Vice President Tokuichi Uranishi said. (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim )